 direct descendant, reflect on Garrison as a political activist, an internationalist, an advocate of feminism, and more. Together they present a new appraisal of one of America’s most challenging, inspiring, and controversial historical figures.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAbolitionistszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aAntislavery movementszUnited StatesxHistoryy19th century. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Political.2bisacsh1 aBlackett, Richardj. M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlight, David W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrown, Lois A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarrison, Lloyd McKim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaurie, Bruce, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStewart, James Brewer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStewart, James Brewer, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030013658640uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030015240140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300152401423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300152401/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY